raw_text = "~ start
Broken Installer: ERROR! ERROR!
Broken Installer: Missing dependency! Missing libsupport.so!
Broken Installer: [hyperventilating in binary]

- Calm down
	Broken Installer: I CANNOT CALM WITHOUT DEPENDENCIES!
	Broken Installer: Do you understand? Nothing compiles without the right libraries!
	- What libraries?
		Broken Installer: Look: libsupport.so, libutils.a, libcommon.so
		Broken Installer: Each one a necessary foundation. Each one interconnected.
		Broken Installer: It's called the dependency tree. Break a branch, everything falls.
- What do you need?
	Broken Installer: A package manager! apt, pacman, dnf, zypper—ANY of them!
	Broken Installer: They resolve dependencies automatically.
	Broken Installer: apt install clears /etc/apt/sources.list
	Broken Installer: pacman -Sy updates the mirror database first
	Broken Installer: But first: you must know what each does!
	Broken Installer: Update the system! Fetch the dependencies! FIX ME!
- Ignore
	Broken Installer: SYSTEM WILL BREAK FURTHER!!!
	Broken Installer: Broken dependencies spread like corruption

- Understand dependencies?
	Broken Installer: When you install software, it needs libraries.
	Broken Installer: Libraries are code that other programs reuse.
	Broken Installer: If a library is missing, nothing that depends on it can run!
	Broken Installer: Package managers track versions and compatibility.
	Broken Installer: They prevent the chaos that I am experiencing now.

Broken Installer: Learn how to install packages properly.
Broken Installer: Understand dependency resolution.
Broken Installer: Then maybe… I can compile again. I can be whole.
=> END
"
metadata/dialogue_manager_version = "3.9.0"
